<item>
            <title>[LU-9798] split recovery-mds-scale into two test sets: recovery-mds-scale and recovery-ost-scale</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9798</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We would like to have the MDS and OST failover tests that are run by recovery-mds-scale to be run by two separate test sets:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;recovery-mds-scale&lt;br/&gt;
recovery-ost-scale&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was successfully tested with patches 28155 and 28195.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With 28155, the following lines in recovery-mds-scale were removed:&lt;br/&gt;
239 test_failover_ost() &lt;/p&gt;
{
240     # failover a random OST
241     failover_target OST
242 }
&lt;p&gt;243 run_test failover_ost &quot;failover OST&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
244&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With 28195, the following lines in recovery-mds-scale were removed:&lt;br/&gt;
233 test_failover_mds() &lt;/p&gt;
{
234     # failover a random MDS
235     failover_target MDS
236 }
&lt;p&gt;237 run_test failover_mds &quot;failover MDS&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
238 &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>any config that is tested with recovery-mds-scale</environment>
